## 1. Purpose
This policy defines the acceptable and prohibited uses of [COMPANY]'s information systems, data, networks, and devices. It protects [COMPANY], its workforce, and the individuals whose PHI it handles by setting clear expectations for responsible use, so that productivity does not come at the cost of confidentiality, integrity, or availability.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all workforce members and contractors and to all use of [COMPANY] systems, accounts, data, and devices — corporate-owned and, where permitted, personal devices used for work (BYOD). It covers the production SaaS application, [AWS], [Snowflake], [GitHub], email, [Slack] and other collaboration tools, endpoints, and networks.

## 3. Policy — Acceptable Use
1. Systems, accounts, and data **shall** be used only for authorized [COMPANY] business purposes and only with access granted under `../access/access-control-policy.md.template`.
2. Each user **shall** safeguard their credentials, use [SSO/MFA] where available, and **shall not** share accounts or credentials.
3. Data **shall** be handled according to its classification (`data-classification-and-handling.md.template`); PHI **shall** be accessed only on a minimum-necessary, need-to-know basis.
4. Users **shall** use only [approved/sanctioned applications and services] for [COMPANY] data; introducing unapproved software or services (shadow IT) that touches [COMPANY] data **shall** require approval.
5. Devices used for work **shall** meet endpoint security requirements (encryption, screen lock, current patches, [MDM/EDR]) per `../operations/endpoint-security-policy.md.template`.
6. Users **shall** report lost/stolen devices, suspected incidents, and suspected PHI exposure immediately per `../resilience/incident-response-plan.md.template`.
7. Users have **no expectation of privacy** in their use of [COMPANY] systems; usage may be monitored and logged for security and compliance, subject to applicable law.

## 4. Prohibited Use
The following are **prohibited**:
1. **Placing PHI or Restricted data in unauthorized tools or locations** — personal or non-approved email, unsanctioned [Slack] channels/DMs, personal cloud storage (e.g., personal Drive/Dropbox), personal devices not authorized for it, USB/portable media, or unapproved third-party/AI services.
2. Pasting PHI, secrets, or Confidential data into **public or unapproved generative-AI / external tools**.
3. Exporting, copying, or downloading PHI to local machines or uncontrolled locations except as explicitly authorized.
4. Hardcoding secrets/credentials in code, [GitHub] repositories, tickets, or chat; secrets belong in [the approved secrets manager].
5. Disabling, bypassing, or tampering with security controls (encryption, logging, MFA, endpoint agents).
6. Using [COMPANY] systems for illegal activity, harassment, or to access/transmit unlawful or offensive content.
7. Unauthorized access attempts, scanning, or testing of systems beyond one's authorization.
8. Connecting unauthorized devices/services to production environments ([AWS]/[Snowflake]).
9. Sharing Restricted data externally without authorization and, for PHI, an executed BAA (`../vendor/third-party-risk-management-policy.md.template`).

## 5. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns this policy; defines approved tools; monitors compliance. |
| [Head of People / HR] | Ensures acknowledgment at onboarding and annually; administers sanctions. |
| Managers | Reinforce acceptable use; approve tool/access requests appropriately. |
| All Workforce / Contractors | Read, acknowledge, and comply; report violations and incidents. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template`.

## 6. Acknowledgment
All workforce members and contractors **shall** acknowledge this policy at onboarding and at least [annually]. Acknowledgment records are retained as evidence (`../people/security-awareness-training-policy.md.template`).

## 7. Exceptions
Exceptions (e.g., authorized use of a non-standard tool) require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log.

## 8. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Use of [COMPANY] systems may be monitored and logged. Violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template` and, for PHI mishandling, the HIPAA workforce sanctions process (`../healthcare/sanctions-policy.md.template`); placing PHI in unauthorized tools may also trigger the breach assessment process (`../healthcare/hipaa-breach-notification-procedure.md.template`). Sanctions range up to and including termination and legal action.

